<p><b><a name="Where you can find these items:"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Where you can find these items:</font></a></b></p>
<div align="center">
  <table border="0" cellspacing="1" width="100%" height="1">
    <tr>
      <td width="86%" height="136" valign="top" align="left"><font face="Verdana" size="2">You can purchase
        all of these items off pottery venders which are located in most major
        towns. I bought mine in <a href="http://www.everlore.com/geography/default.asp?MAPID=1152&Go=Go">Kelethin</a>
        from "Merchant Legweren", Here is what he looks
        like:                                                    
        <p>He is located on the on the platform directly to the right of the
        platform that the" main lift" goes up to. ( the "main
        lift" is also known as the priest lift) On the same platform as the
        worriers guild.</p>
        <p>If you are really serious, it would be a good ideal to to travel to
        "<a href="http://www.everlore.com/geography/default.asp?MAPID=2243&Go=Go">Beholders
        Maze, in The Gorge of King Xorbb</a>" and hunt muddeites. The loot
        that they drop is 80% clay. Bring allot of backpacks and load up, and
        when you get to encumbered then you can travel to <a href="http://www.everlore.com/geography/default.asp?MAPID=1154&Go=Go">Rivervale</a>,
        and put the clay in the bank.</p>
        <p><b>Clay Conversion Chart:</b> (as told by the in game guide book, doesn't
        make much sense to me)</font></td>
