<p align="center"><a href="#Pottery:">Top</a></p>
<p><b><a name="How to make your first pot:"><font face="Verdana" size="2">How to make your first pot:</font></a></b></p>
<p><font face="Verdana" size="2">Once you have collected the basic items needed to make a pottery item, then
next thing you need to do is locate a pottery and a kiln. These are also located
in most major towns. Here is what they look like:</font></p>
<div align="center">
  <table border="3" cellspacing="1" width="60%" height="62" bordercolorlight="#C0C0C0" bordercolordark="#666666">
    <tr>
      <td width="22%" height="19" valign="middle" align="center"><b><a name="Kiln">Kiln</a></b></td>
      <td width="78%" height="19" valign="middle" align="center"><b><a name="Pottery Wheel">Pottery
        Wheel</a></b></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width="22%" height="31"><img border="0" src="http://www.everlore.com/files/Oven_I_think.jpg" width="200" height="386"></td>
      <td width="78%" height="31" align="center"><img border="0" src="http://www.everlore.com/files/Pottery_Kiln.jpg" width="275" height="197"></td>
    </tr>
  </table>
</div>
<p> </p>
<div align="center">
  <table border="0" cellspacing="1" width="100%">
    <tr>
      <td width="14%"><img border="0" src="http://www.everlore.com/files/Pottery%20Wheel_inside.jpg" width="118" height="292"></td>
      <td width="104%" valign="top" align="left"><font face="Verdana" size="2">We recommend that the first
        items you attempt to make be a <a href="#Clay Jar">clay jar</a>, and for
        this you will have need to of purchased the the appropriate
        sketch. 
        <p>Approach the <a href="#Pottery Wheel">pottery wheel</a> first and right
        click on it. This will open a window that looks like the one at right.
        Place with in this window the sketch, 1 flask of water, and an appropriate
        amount of clay. Then press the "combine" button at the bottom
        of the window. If you succeeded than a raw product will be placed into
        your inventory if you have failed then they what you placed within the
        wheel will be destroyed in the attempt. Your not done.</p>
        <p>Now go to the <a href="#Kiln">kiln</a> and and right click on it and
        on it. This will open a window like the one at right. Place with in the
        window the raw product, and the appropriate firing sheet, for a clay jug
        you will want to use a quality firing sheet. And if you have succeeded
        than a clay jug will be placed into you inventory, if not than the
        firing sheet and the raw product will be destroyed in the attempt.</p>
        <p>This is the basic procedure that you will fallow to create all
        pottery items.</font></td>
      <td width="17%"><img border="0" src="http://www.everlore.com/files/Kiln%20_inside.jpg" width="117" height="292"></td>
    </tr>
  </table>
</div>
