<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><b><a name="Introduction:">Introduction:</a></b></p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Pottery
in my opinion a very valuable and under used trade skill. It has a great potential
for profit gain because other trade skill require what you can make while
potting. However pottery can be very expensive when beginning, because it is
very component intensive (that is to say that there are many thing to buy). And
pottery is one of the only multiple step skills, so you will fail quite often in
the beginning. When you decide to undertake the rigors of the professional
potting scene, the very first thing you must do is invest at least 10 practice
points into your potting skill. This is <a href="http://www.everlore.com">Everlore</a>'s
policy in almost all trade skills as it will save you money, time, and trade
skill components.</font></p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"> </p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font face="Verdana" size="2"><b><a name="What you need to make your first pot:">What
you need to make your first pot:</a></b></font></p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"> </p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font face="Verdana" size="2">There
are quite a lot of items you will need to purchase
in order to make your first pot. Here is a list: </font></p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"> </p>
